{
  "texts": [
    "WavefunctionsThe \"primitive\" IKS state is that at |ν| = 3, since this corresponds to a filling of a single electron or hole band of the central octet.",
    "The Hartree-Fock projector of the ν = -3 IKS state is parameterized in the boosted frame in the Chern basis (see Section 4.1) asP-3 (k, k ′) = 1 8 (1 + s z)(1 + n ⊥ k • γ)(1 + m k • η)δ k,k ′(107)where the inter-and intra-Chern Pauli triplets γ, η were introduced previously in ( 97).Here, n, m are unit three-vectors, with ⊥ denoting components in the xy-plane, and n z = 0.",
    "Several comments are in order.",
    "(1) It is easy to see that tr P-3 (k, k) = 1 = (ν + 4) as expected; the projector at ν = 3 is given by particle-hole conjugation.",
    "(2) Note that we have partially fixed the gauge of the Chern basis by requiring Ĉ2z to act as σ x τ x and T as τ x K; this means that n ⊥ k and the in-plane components of m k are formally gauge-variant."
  ]
}